"I came to bless not the place, but the people" answered calmly St. Porphyrios.

Saint Porphyrius spent most of his life in the Greek capital, serving in the chapel of the hospital in a dangerous neighbourhood, famous for the high number of prostitutes, drug addicts, and homeless people. 

He talked to all of them as equals and saved many souls there.
